132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1196
S.P. 485 In Senate, March 20, 2025
Resolve, to Require the Towns of Kittery and York to Develop a
Boundary Description
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator LAWRENCE of York.
Cosponsored by Representative SARGENT of York and
Representatives: MATHIESON of Kittery, MEYER of Eliot, RUNTE of York.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Development of boundary description for Kittery and York.
2 Resolved: That the Town of Kittery and the Town of York shall jointly develop a
3 description, in metes and bounds, of the boundary between the 2 towns that reflects the
4 current boundary as understood in each town's respective assessing maps for all parcels
5 along the presently recognized boundary.
6 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That the Town of Kittery and the Town of York shall
7 jointly submit, no later than December 3, 2025, the description of the boundary between
8 the 2 towns as developed pursuant to section 1 to the Joint Standing Committee on State
9 and Local Government. The committee may report out a bill based on the description
10 establishing a boundary between the towns of Kittery and York to the Second Regular
11 Session of the 132nd Legislature.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This resolve requires the Town of Kittery and the Town of York to jointly develop a
1144 description, in metes and bounds, of the boundary between the 2 towns based on the
1155 assessing maps in each of the towns. The towns are required to jointly provide the
1166 description to the Joint Standing Committee on State and Local Government, which may
1177 report out a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature establishing the
1188 boundary between the 2 towns.
